<p class="MsoNormal">I’m compiling hwloc using clang (bgclang&#43;&#43;11 from ANL) to run on IO nodes af a BGQ. It seems to have compiled ok, and when I run lstopo, I get an output like this (below), which looks reasonable, but there are 15 sockets instead of 16.
 I’m a little worried because the first time I compiled, I had problems where apps would report an error from HWLOC on start and tell me to set HWLOC_FORCE_BGQ=1. when I did set this env var, it would then report that “topology became empty” and the app would
 segfault due to the unexpected return from hwloc presumably.<o:p></o:p></p>
